[[File:WilstMolan.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Wilst Molan wore Thoadeye-style makeup.]]
'''Thoadeye-style makeup''' was a style of makeup<ref name="aotcvis">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> that originated from<ref name="Planetnamia">{{Planetnamia|other=Thoadeye-style makeup|system=Thoadeye [[Star system/Legends|system]]|legends=1}}</ref> the [[Thoadeye system/Legends|Thoadeye system]] in the [[Deep Core/Legends|Deep Core]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> It consisted of dark lines<ref name="aotcvis" /> and cosmetic beadwork surrounding one of the wearer's [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="Who's Who">{{InsiderCite|75|Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night}}</ref> 

During a [[Local day/Legends|night]]<ref name="aotc" /> in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|woman]] [[Wilst Molan]]<ref name="DB">{{DB|character|wilstmolan|Molan, Wilst}}"</ref> wore the makeup style to the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="aotc" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="FF">{{FactFile|96|OUT 1-2|Outlander Nightclub Patrons}}</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="CSWE2" /> While the makeup and her outfit were striking, it did not match the charisma of the outfit of her acquaintance [[Nyrat Agira/Legends|Nyrat Agira]], a woman who Molan vied with for the unofficial title of "best-dressed Outlander patron."<ref name="FF" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Ep2VDcover.jpg|thumb|right|200px|''Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary'' provided a name for thoadeye-style makeup.]]
Thoadeye-style makeup first appeared in the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']],<ref name="aotc">{{Film|II}}</ref> which released on [[May 16]], [[2002]].<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year by Year: A Visual Chronicle]]''</ref> The makeup was first pictured before the film's release in the documentary "[[Making Episode II Webdocs|A Twinkle Beyond Pluto]],"<ref name="ATBP">{{SW|url=video/a-twinkle-beyond-pluto|series=Making Episode II Webdocs|text=Part 5: A Twinkle Beyond Pluto}}</ref> released on [[July 31]], [[2001]],<ref name="ATBP Date">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/me2/archive.html|text=''Making Episode II Webdocs'' archive}}</ref> and first identified in the reference book ''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]'',<ref name="aotcvis" /> written by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]] and released on [[April 23]], 2002.<ref name="VDRelease">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/ref/news20020227.html|text=Book Preview: DK Episode II Books}}</ref> 

The [[The Official Star Wars Fact File 96|ninety-sixth issue]] of ''[[The Official Star Wars Fact File]]'' magazine,<ref name="FF" /> written by [[Iain Lowson]]<ref name="FF Author">{{LinkedIn|url=in/iainlowson|text=Iain Lowson|archivefile=File:IainLowson-LinkedIn.png}}</ref> and released on [[October 29]], [[2003]],<ref name="FFDate">{{FFdates|96}}</ref> provided the capitalization of the makeup, but spelled it as "thoadeye-style make-up."<ref name="FF" /> In the article "[[Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night]]," written by [[Daniel Wallace]] and published in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth]] issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]''<ref name="Who's Who" /> on [[April 6]], [[2004]],<ref name="SW.com2">{{SWArchive|url=community/fanclub/mag/news20040315.html|text=The New Face of Evil}}</ref> the makeup is incorrectly spelled as "thodeye style."<ref name="Who's Who">{{InsiderCite|75|Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night}}</ref>

